        <description>Neutronium is an extradimensional matter that does not fit anywhere on the periodic table. Its properties seem to shift without meaning, flowing freely between gas, liquid, and solid, sometimes all at the same exact moment and must be contained in a hardy container. Fortunately, this makes Neutronium incredibly light, even lighter than Quasar Alloy. It by itself can not be used in normal construction or be intergrated in any technology.\n\nHowever, it is a vital ingredient in the most advanced Quasar-tier weaponry and buildings, and high volumes almost always must be used.</description>
